SELECT 
    a.CODE, 
    COUNT(DISTINCT p.Id) AS patient_count, 
    COUNT(CASE WHEN a.REACTION1 = 1 THEN 1 ELSE NULL END) AS severe_reaction_count, 
    ROUND(COUNT(CASE WHEN a.REACTION1 = 1 THEN 1 ELSE NULL END) * 1.0 / COUNT(DISTINCT p.Id), 4) AS survival_chance
FROM 
    allergies a
JOIN 
    patients p ON a.PATIENT = p.Id
WHERE 
    a.CODE = (SELECT CODE FROM allergies WHERE SYSTEM = 'Wheat')
GROUP BY 
    a.CODE;

question: When was the allergy with the code 782576004 recorded?
What are the survival chances of allgery Aspirin?
answers:
SELECT 
    a.CODE, 
    COUNT(DISTINCT p.Id) AS total_patients, 
    COUNT(CASE WHEN a.REACTION1 IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE NULL END) AS severe_reaction, 
    ROUND(COUNT(CASE WHEN a.REACTION1 IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE NULL END) * 1.0 / COUNT(DISTINCT p.Id), 4) AS survival_chance
FROM 
    allergies a
JOIN 
    patients p ON a.PATIENT = p.Id
WHERE 
    a.CODE = 'Aspirin'
GROUP BY 
    a.CODE;

What is the cost of the immunization Influenza  seasonal  injectable  preservative free?
What is the successrate of medication 72 HR Fentanyl 0.025 MG/HR Transdermal System?
answers:
SELECT 
    (SUM(CASE WHEN m.DESCRIPTION = '72 HR Fentanyl 0.025 MG/HR Transdermal System' AND m.BASE_COST > 0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / 
     COUNT(CASE WHEN m.DESCRIPTION = '72 HR Fentanyl 0.025 MG/HR Transdermal System' THEN 1 END)) * 100 AS success_rate
FROM 
    medications m
JOIN 
    encounters e ON m.ENCOUNTER = e.Id
JOIN 
    patients p ON e.PATIENT = p.Id;
